    {
      "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-80f3-9389-fa5d157eeef3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors look to explore how SRL can lead to performance by having 140 online students and 466 b-learning students fill the MSLQ. The results show that B-Learning students engage more in help-seeking and peer-learning, while online students engage more in SRL behavior on the remaining constructs. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-80f3-9389-fa5d157eeef3",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "d580024f-f391-49e3-b50e-212c7b33c520"
        },
        "created_time": "2025-02-03T22:26:00.000Z",
        "last_edited_time": "2025-02-03T22:27:00.000Z",
        "created_by": {
          "object": "user",
          "id": "20a7795c-3622-4527-bd13-5ddbf48dc31d"
        },
        "last_edited_by": {
          "object": "user",
          "id": "20a7795c-3622-4527-bd13-5ddbf48dc31d"
        },
        "has_children": false,
        "in_trash": false,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "paragraph": {
          "rich_text": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": {
                "content": "The authors look to explore how SRL can lead to performance by having 140 online students and 466 b-learning students fill the MSLQ. The results show that B-Learning students engage more in help-seeking and peer-learning, while online students engage more in SRL behavior on the remaining constructs. ",
                "link": null
              },
              "annotations": {
                "bold": false,
                "italic": false,
                "strikethrough": false,
                "underline": false,
                "code": false,
                "color": "default"
              },
              "plain_text": "The authors look to explore how SRL can lead to performance by having 140 online students and 466 b-learning students fill the MSLQ. The results show that B-Learning students engage more in help-seeking and peer-learning, while online students engage more in SRL behavior on the remaining constructs. ",
              "href": null
            }
          ],
          "icon": null,
          "color": "default"
        },
        "archived": false
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-8097-a8bc-ed0513b7091a",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Moreover, the authors found that, whether online or in B-Learning, there were no significant differences when it comes to the predictive power of different SRL constructs. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "18f4750c-f3ba-8097-a8bc-ed0513b7091a",
        "parent": {
